<p>Now when Symfony loads, it'll load everything from <code>config.yml</code>, but it'll also call
this function, and we can control whatever extra configuration we want. In <code>config.yml</code>,
we can't have the <code>web_profiler</code> stuff because this file is <em>always</em> loaded. Remove
that:</p>
<p>[[ code('7dc1f3ad36') ]]</p>
<p>But inside the Closure, we can say: if we're in the <code>dev</code> environment, then call
<code>$container-&gt;loadFromExtension()</code> to pass in the configuration we want. Use <code>web_profiler</code>
as the first agument and an array as the second with <code>toolbar =&gt; true</code>:</p>
